    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>BALLY'S EXPANSION</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Angela Starita</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Starita, Angela</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Bally's Park Place in Atlantic City, NJ, plans to open 9,400-square-foot addition on Labor Day weekend (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Bally's Park Place will open a 9,400-square-foot addition containing 340 slot machines on Labor Day weekend. The room, called Coyote Kate's Slot Parlor, is an expansion of Bally's Wild Wild West Casino, which opened in 1997. The addition will also include a bakery, a retail store, and such western memorabilia as a bearskin coat worn by Wyatt Earp. The expansion cost about $25 million. The parent company, Park Place Entertainment, also spent $5 million to add meeting rooms its Caesars Atlantic City. The addition will connect Wild Wild West Casino to Caesars by an escalator.</p>
        <p>Angela Starita</p>
      </block>
